{{infobox Chinese|l=Yin Earth Rabbit|kanji=己卯|romaji=tsuchinoto usagi|onyomi=kibō|p=jǐmǎo|w=chi-mao|mi=t͡ɕi³⁵ mɑʊ̯²¹|y=gei2 maau5|j=gei2 maau5|ci=kei maːu̯|mc=kɨj maw|oc-bs=kɯʔ maw}}
{{Sexagenary cycle comprehensive}}
'''Yin Earth Rabbit also known as 己卯''' (tsuchinotou, kidonousagi, kidonou, kibou) is one of the elements of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支}}.

It is the 16th combination of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支}}, preceded by {{ill|Bodonotora|ja|戊寅}} and followed by {{ill|Koushin|ja|庚辰}}. In the framework of {{ill|Yin Yang Five Elements Thought|ja|陰陽五行思想}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|十干}} symbol {{ill|Ki|ja|己|1=Tsuchinoto (己)}} represents yin {{ill|Earth|ja|土}}, while the {{ill|Earthly Branches|ja|十二支}} symbol {{ill|Rabbit|ja|卯|1=Rabbit (zodiac)|lt=Rabbit (卯)}} represents yin {{ill|Wood|ja|木}}, establishing a restraining relationship ({{ill|Mutual Restraint|ja|五行思想#相剋（そうこく）}}) (i.e. Wood overcomes Earth).

