'''Yin Earth Rabbit also known as 己卯''' (tsuchinotou, kidonousagi, kidonou, kibou) is one of the elements of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支}}.

It is the 16th combination of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支}}, preceded by {{ill|Bodonotora|ja|戊寅}} and followed by {{ill|Koushin|ja|庚辰}}. In the framework of {{ill|Yin Yang Five Elements Thought|ja|陰陽五行思想|1=Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|十干}} symbol {{ill|Ki|ja|己|1=Tsuchinoto (己)}} represents yin {{ill|Earth|ja|土}}, while the {{ill|Earthly Branches|ja|十二支}} symbol {{ill|Rabbit|ja|卯|1=Rabbit (zodiac)|lt=Rabbit (卯)}} represents yin {{ill|Wood|ja|木}}, establishing a restraining relationship ({{ill|Mutual Restraint|ja|五行思想#相剋（そうこく）}}) (i.e. Wood overcomes Earth).

==Yin Earth Rabbit (己卯)'s Years==
A year in the {{ill|Western calendar|ja|西暦}} that leaves a remainder of 19 when divided by 60 is a {{ill|year|ja|年}} of {{ill|Kibou|ja|己卯}}.
