{{infobox Chinese|l=Yin Earth Rabbit|kanji=己卯|romaji=tsuchinoto usagi|onyomi=kibō|p=jǐmǎo|w=chi-mao|mi=t͡ɕi³⁵ mɑʊ̯²¹|y=gei2 maau5|j=gei2 maau5|ci=kei maːu̯|mc=kɨj maw|oc-bs=kɯʔ maw}}
{{Sexagenary cycle comprehensive}}
'''Yin Earth Rabbit also known as 己卯''' (tsuchinotou, kidonousagi, kidonou, kibou) is one of the elements of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支|12=draft|12=draft}}.

It is the 16th combination of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支|12=draft|12=draft}}, preceded by {{ill|Bodonotora|ja|戊寅|12=draft|12=draft}} and followed by {{ill|Koushin|ja|庚辰|12=draft|12=draft}}. In the framework of {{ill|Yin Yang Five Elements Thought|ja|陰陽五行思想|1=Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|12=draft|12=draft}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|十干|12=draft|12=draft}} symbol {{ill|Ki|ja|己|1=Tsuchinoto (己)|12=draft|12=draft}} represents yin {{ill|Earth|ja|土|12=draft|12=draft}}, while the {{ill|Earthly Branches|ja|十二支|12=draft|12=draft}} symbol {{ill|Rabbit|ja|卯|1=Rabbit (zodiac)|lt=Rabbit (卯)|12=draft|12=draft}} represents yin {{ill|Wood|ja|木|12=draft|12=draft}}, establishing a restraining relationship ({{ill|Mutual Restraint|ja|五行思想#相剋（そうこく）|12=draft|12=draft}}) (i.e. Wood overcomes Earth).

==Yin Earth Rabbit (己卯)'s Years==
A year in the {{ill|Western calendar|ja|西暦|12=draft|12=draft}} that leaves a remainder of 19 when divided by 60 is a {{ill|year|ja|年|12=draft|12=draft}} of {{ill|Kibou|ja|己卯|12=draft|12=draft}}.
